betterquesting.name: Trials and Tree-bulations
betterquesting.desc: We all have to start somewhere. Get out there and start punching some trees!

betterquesting.name: Grout things are happening
betterquesting.desc: Now that you've gathered your supplies, and put on your fancy new armor. we can start cookin' with gas baby!

betterquesting.name: Compacting your storage
betterquesting.desc:
Building a Compacting Drawer allows you to place ingots or nuggets into it and take out their next step, providing you've placed enough of it's lower tier.

Keep in mind, the Top Half of the drawer is what counts towards the maximum stack.

betterquesting.name: Trimming your storage
betterquesting.desc: Drawer trimming allows you to extend the range of your drawers around corners. This does not however, extend the 12 block radius from the drawer controller.

betterquesting.name: Customizing your storage
betterquesting.desc: Craft a Framing Table. This will allow you to crate custom Storage Drawers that fit your particular build. We'll provide the frames.

betterquesting.name: Upgrading your storage.
betterquesting.desc: Using drawer upgrades exponentially increases how much can go into them. Craft up some void upgrades in case you go over the limit anyway.

betterquesting.name: Seared to perfection
betterquesting.desc: Try laying the grout down and veinmining it with your Furnace Armor on.

betterquesting.name: Cast it aside
betterquesting.desc:
Add some gold ore to the smeltery or alloy some aluminum brass to create some casts.

Lay some stone tinker's parts on your casting table and let the gold flow over it.

betterquesting.name: I am the Sword
betterquesting.desc: You are the blade, you are the dream of the brave.

betterquesting.name: Controlling your storage
betterquesting.desc: A drawer controller will allow you to place any item into a drawer that is connected to it. The range of this action is a 12 block radius.

betterquesting.name: Are you sensing a pattern?
betterquesting.desc: We've given you more than enough patterns to get you started. Put them on your stencil table and create the following stencils?

betterquesting.name: Smelter? I hardly know her!
betterquesting.desc: If you're going to get your smeltery up and running, you're going to need to gather the supplies.

betterquesting.name: Tinker Toys
betterquesting.desc: The basis of any modpack is setting up your Tinker Tools quick, fast and in a hurry.

betterquesting.name: Collecting stone again!?
betterquesting.desc: Why would we have you collecting cobblestone?

betterquesting.name: Coming to a head
betterquesting.desc:
Your patterns are made, now lets get to making your tools. With any luck they'll be with you a while.

Don't worry that their made of stone, you can upgrade any part of your tool at the Tool Station or use them to make casts at your smeltery.

betterquesting.name: Going to the Market
betterquesting.desc: The market block will allow you to purchase Pam's Harvestcraft Seeds for the low low price of one emerald each. These seeds will become very handy later on when you get into the Avarita mod. I recommend saving up now.

betterquesting.name: Where's the Beef?
betterquesting.desc: Try to find some vanilla cows. Herd them together and breed them to get some raw steakage.

betterquesting.name: Experimenting with Modifiers
betterquesting.desc: Collect some redstone and lapis to increase your tool's usefullness.

betterquesting.name: The Key to someone's heart
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have some vanilla farms ready to go, and a solid food supply, you can start using the Kitchen accessories to generate greater foods to sustain you.

betterquesting.name: Creeping Death
betterquesting.desc: Go out and test your new sword on some nasties.

betterquesting.name: A pack for your back
betterquesting.desc:
Craft up a backpack. We'll throw in some upgrades for you.

If you set up the correct keybinding, you can equip and open it without taking up an inventory slot.

betterquesting.name: Making the most of your pack
betterquesting.desc: Your backpack is pretty small to begin with, why don't you upgrade it to make better use of it?

betterquesting.name: Early Eats
betterquesting.desc: A simple quest to get you some simple food. Bon Appetit!

betterquesting.name: Basic Storage
betterquesting.desc: Craft a couple of storage drawers. Don't worry, you'll be crafting a lot more.

betterquesting.name: Mine your own business
betterquesting.desc:
Now that you have some furnace armor, you can auto-smelt whatever you mine from now on. Be warned, having the effect turned on will affect durability. 

Take it out for a spin. Grab some ingots and We'll give you some ores for when your smeltery's done.

§4Make sure to turn off the armor whenever you mine coal, unless you reaaally want creosote.

betterquesting.name: The Angry Mob
betterquesting.desc: Start crafting the basics you'll need for your manual mob farm. Mob farms are going to be your primary source of loot bags for a while.

betterquesting.name: War Ensemble
betterquesting.desc: If you really want to add some defense to your base, look no further than Turrets!

betterquesting.name: Trials and Tree-bulations
betterquesting.desc: You should know the drill by now. Start punching some trees. Collect a good surplus of wood and we can go from there.

betterquesting.name: Tinkering your Tools
betterquesting.desc: SO you have your basic Tinker's setup. Lets show you what else this mod can do.

betterquesting.name: Woot Woot
betterquesting.desc: Tired of your basic Mob Farm?

betterquesting.name: Agricraft Agglomerations
betterquesting.desc: Agricraft comes with a lot of grindy goodies. Using it with Mystical Agriculture is the best way to maximize your crop production.

betterquesting.name: Fight for your right to Party
betterquesting.desc: Make your base an inpenetrable fortress and protect yourself from the denizens of your world.

betterquesting.name: Mystical Agriculture
betterquesting.desc: Crops that can give you any resource you want.
